From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Subject: [PATCH] dts: orangepi-zero: appliance trim - disable unused USB-host/wifi/eth

This headless USB-gadget appliance uses only the musb OTG (gadget) and the
USB-A host port. Disable the unused blocks:
 - ehci0/ohci0 (OTG host companion on the shared PHY0): disabling releases
   PHY0 to musb so the gadget enumerates (armbian #8871 root cause) AND skips
   their probe/enumeration, trimming kernel boot.
 - mmc1 (XR819 SDIO wifi) and emac (ethernet): unused.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-zero.dts	2026-06-27 14:31:46.167330903 +0200
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-zero.dts	2026-06-27 14:31:46.176197749 +0200
@@ -124,7 +124,9 @@
 };
 
 &ehci0 {
-	status = "okay";
+	/* OTG host companion (PHY0): unused - the OTG port is the musb
+	 * gadget. Disabling releases PHY0 to musb and trims USB boot time. */
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &ehci1 {
@@ -135,7 +137,8 @@
 	phy-handle = <&int_mii_phy>;
 	phy-mode = "mii";
 	allwinner,leds-active-low;
-	status = "okay";
+	/* ethernet unused on this appliance */
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &mmc0 {
@@ -152,7 +155,8 @@
 	bus-width = <4>;
 	max-frequency = <16000000>;
 	non-removable;
-	status = "okay";
+	/* wifi unused; disabling removes its SDIO init at boot */
+	status = "disabled";
 
 	/*
 	 * Explicitly define the sdio device, so that we can add an ethernet
@@ -171,7 +175,7 @@
 };
 
 &ohci0 {
-	status = "okay";
+	status = "disabled";
 };
 
 &ohci1 {
